<DocLayout title="Cookie Policy" description="Cookie policy for AEGIS Initiative websites.">
  <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>

  <p><em>Last updated: March 21, 2026</em></p>

  <p>
    This Cookie Policy explains how cookies and similar technologies are used on AEGIS Initiative websites. For broader
    data practices, see <a href="/legal/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <h2>What Are Cookies?</h2>

  <p>
    Cookies are small data files placed on your device when you visit a website. They are widely used to make websites
    function correctly and to provide operational information to site owners.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <h2>How We Use Cookies</h2>

  <p>
    AEGIS Initiative websites are static documentation sites. We do not set first-party cookies, operate behavioral
    tracking, serve targeted advertising, or use web beacons or tracking pixels.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong>, which hosts the Services, may set cookies as part of their infrastructure and
    security services &mdash; including bot detection and DDoS mitigation. These cookies are strictly necessary for site
    operation and are governed by the
    <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare Privacy
    Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <h2>How to Control Cookies</h2>

  <p>
    You can control cookies through your browser settings. For instructions, visit your browser&rsquo;s help
    documentation. Note that restricting Cloudflare&rsquo;s infrastructure cookies may affect site availability or
    performance.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Updates to This Policy</h2>

  <p>
    We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time. The date at the top of this page reflects the most recent
    revision.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <p>
    <em>AEGIS&trade;</em> | <em>&ldquo;Capability without constraint is not intelligence&rdquo;&trade;</em><br />
    <em>AEGIS Initiative &mdash; Finnoybu IP LLC</em>
  </p>
</DocLayout>
